answers.body_markdown:
As the stack trace suggested, the error is thrown when `BufferedWriter.close` is calling `ZipOutputStream.write`. This is because `BufferedWriter`, as its name suggested, is buffered. Data written by a `BufferedWriter` may not necessarily be written into the file immediately. When a `BufferedWriter` get closed (in this case closed by try-with-resources), it will flush all unwritten data, by that time your `ZipEntry` has already been closed so that&#39;s why the error.

The solution is to manually call `writer.flush()` before `zipOutputStream.closeEntry()`

```java
public void createZip(Path source) throws Exception {
    try (ZipOutputStream zipOutputStream = new ZipOutputStream(Files.newOutputStream(zipFile));
            BufferedWriter writer = new BufferedWriter(new OutputStreamWriter(zipOutputStream))) {

        String entry = source.getFileName().toString();
        System.out.println(entry);
        zipOutputStream.putNextEntry(new ZipEntry(source.getFileName().toString()));

        try (BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(Files.newInputStream(source)))) {
            while (reader.ready()) {
                writer.write(reader.readLine());
            }
        }
        writer.flush(); //Add this line!!
        zipOutputStream.closeEntry();
    } catch (IOException e) {
        e.printStackTrace();
    }
}

```

